data.title: My version of "Cheers!"
data.text: I don't live in El Cajon, but am downtown fairly frequently.  I usually have a coffee break at this Starbucks, and am always greated as if I were one of the family.  Great service, friendly conversation if you want it, and of course, great coffee.

data.title: Close in the neighborhood
data.text: My favorite at Starbucks is the Green Tea Frapp with no extra sweetner. I understand the current mix has been sweetened. At the holidays they sometimes have the Black Cherry flavoring to add. But the store is so small that if we did not live in Southern CA, I would never go there. There is outside seating, but not very private for conversation can be heard by those entering and exiting the store.

data.title: Frappachino Please
data.text: A nice place to get a hot or cold drink. Restroom facilities are clean. Inside and outside seating, several tables outside. There's always shade outside.

data.title: Parking
data.text: This isn't my nornal starbucks stop in the morning but it's not too far from where I live so I drop in every once in a while. I'm not a big fan of the parking situation. If you're not out on foot on main st, you have to basically park on the back side of the building and walk to the front. A minor inconvenience but in my opinion the drive thru is just alot quicker. Especially when you're trying to get to work in the morning. It wasn't over crowded. Drinks took about 5 mins and the staff was friendly. Gave a 4 star primarily bc of the parking.

data.title: boa parada!
data.text: O Starbucks é bom para um café da tarde rápido, o ambiente é muito legal e com muitas opções de café, não só quentes!
